         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JMR">
            <p> . . . ]according to what was] ordained [[by ? . . ?son of] Hermas the son of Nardos, in which he alone is to be buried and no-one else, neither my heir nor 
            successor, since he who has undertaken to bury anyone else <supplied reason="subaudible">here</supplied> is to pay to the People 3000 denarii and to the imperial 
               <foreign xml:lang="la">fiscus</foreign> 3000 denarii, of which the third part shall belong to the prosecutor. A copy of the inscription is placed in the archives 
            under the stephanephoros M. Antonius Agelaos.</p>
         </div>
